<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10031c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10031c">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10031c"> 31(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> stadion = 125 yds / 125000 <font color="green">[+]</font> 62500 <font color="green">[=]</font> 187<font color="green">[500]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Suidas, lexicographe grec du v<sup>e</sup> si&egrave;cle de notre &egrave;re, dit que les courriers parcouraient d&apos;un trait quinze cents <mark><i>stades</i> (mesure itin&eacute;raire de cent vingt-cinq pas)</mark>. <font color="green">[Suidas, the Greek lexicographer of the 5th Century AD, said that the couriers covered at one go 1,500 stadia (units of measuring distance equivalent to 125 yards).]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 26</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01011i" href="c01all.htm#c01011i">VI.C.01:011(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
